<div id="review_1030685828" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1030685828" />
    <a title="Bonnie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31230559-bonnie"><img alt="Bonnie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1589573456p2/31230559.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1030685828?book_show_action=true">Aug 19, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bonnie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bonnie" href="/user/show/31230559-bonnie">Bonnie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/5986906-an-echo-in-the-darkness">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31230559-bonnie?shelf=library-reading-challenge-2015">library-reading-challenge-2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31230559-bonnie?shelf=the-tbr-pile-2015">the-tbr-pile-2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31230559-bonnie?shelf=2015">2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31230559-bonnie?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31230559-bonnie?shelf=e-reader-challenge-2015">e-reader-challenge-2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31230559-bonnie?shelf=2015-finish-the-series">2015-finish-the-series</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1030685828" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5287039693973977469">Okay, let me just say that I had a lot of mixed emotions about the first book. But this one I have one: LOVE! It is SO GOOD! I loved reading about each of the characters and didn&apos;t want this book to end! It&apos;s going on my faves list! Phenomenol!<br/><br/>Marcus has never forgotten Hadassah. He can&apos;t, he loved her too much. How is he ever going to forget her? The world has lost what it once held for him. Things that he used to love now does nothing for him, except irritate him more. Maybe if he can find the</span>
  <span id="freeText5287039693973977469" style="display:none">Okay, let me just say that I had a lot of mixed emotions about the first book. But this one I have one: LOVE! It is SO GOOD! I loved reading about each of the characters and didn't want this book to end! It's going on my faves list! Phenomenol!<br /><br />Marcus has never forgotten Hadassah. He can't, he loved her too much. How is he ever going to forget her? The world has lost what it once held for him. Things that he used to love now does nothing for him, except irritate him more. Maybe if he can find the God Hadassah loved so much, he can at least ask Him why He let Hadassah die. But finding this God might prove harder than he thought, as He is not one of the temple gods. He cannot be found in a building. So where can he be found?<br /><br />It's been a year and God must have more in store for Hadassah. Hidden behind veils to cover her scars, Hadassah still represents Christ well, loving those around her and making a difference in the lives of those who see no hope. Her light for God shines just as brightly as before! But when it comes time to face the one who sent her to the lions, will her faith and courage fail? <br /><br />Julia's friends have abandoned her. Those who she thought she could trust were not who they seemed. All except one: Hadassah. Hadassah loved her, really loved her, and she threw her to the lions. What has she done? Marcus won't forgive her, her mother can't help her. She is all alone. The temple gods refuse to heal her illness. What hope is there? And who is this mysterious woman who reminds her so much of Hadassah?<br /><br />Phoebe loves God. But she is grieved. Her children are both on a path of destruction. Both are living selfishly and do not see their need for God. But she is unable to help them. Will they find their way to the One who can help them? Or will they continue to not see that their selfish ways can only lead to destruction?<br /><br />As much as I hesitate to recommend the first one for those who don't have a strong stomach, it would be rather difficult to really grasp the story in this second book without having read the first one as this is truly a continuation of it. But this second one, other than the very first chapter, does not have any of the gruesome violence and rampant evil the first one had in abundance. I'd say this second one is worth reading without a doubt!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5287039693973977469" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


